09/12/2003
TIRANA, Albania -- The Chief of Turkish General Staff, General Hilmi Ozkok, starts an official visit to Tirana on Tuesday (9 December), part of a tour that includes stops in Kosovo and Bosnia and Herzegovina.
During his two-day visit in Albania, Ozkok is to meet Defence Minister Pandeli Majko and Chief of Albanian General Staff, Lieutenant General Pellumb Qazimi, Prime Minister Fatos Nano and President Alfred Moisiu.
He is also to visit the Zall Herr Commando Regiment Base and the Kucova Military Airport.
Turkey has helped fund reconstruction there.
(ATA, Anadolu Agency - 08/12/03)
